<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <div class="container page-head">
    <span class="eyebrow">AI-assisted</span>
    <h1>Find your shade</h1>
    <p class="lead">Upload a selfie or use your webcam — we'll sample your skin tone and match it to the closest shade in our collection.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container" style="padding-bottom: 72px;">
    <% if (!shadeCatalog.length) { %>
      <div class="notice" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
        No shades are set up in the catalog yet, so there's nothing to match against. Add shades to a product in the admin panel first.
      </div>
    <% } %>

    <div class="card" id="matcher-remembered" style="display:none; margin-bottom: 24px;">
      <h3 style="font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 4px;">Your saved shades</h3>
      <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 16px;">Skin tone shifts with the seasons for a lot of people — save a summer and a winter reading for a more accurate match year-round.</p>
      <div class="matcher-remembered-grid" id="matcher-remembered-grid"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-2" style="align-items: start;">
      <!-- Capture card -->
      <div class="card">
        <h3 style="font-size: 20px;">1. Capture your photo</h3>

        <div class="notice" style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:10px; margin-bottom:18px;">
          <%- icon('alert') %>
          <span>For best results: use natural daylight (avoid strong yellow/warm indoor bulbs), remove makeup from the sampled area if possible, and face the camera directly with your whole face in frame. Webcam lighting varies a lot from device to device, so this is a helpful starting point, not a calibrated color match — think of it as a first guess to narrow down shades worth swatching in person.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="matcher-tabs">
          <button type="button" class="matcher-tab is-active" data-matcher-tab="upload">Upload photo</button>
          <button type="button" class="matcher-tab" data-matcher-tab="webcam">Use webcam</button>
        </div>

        <div id="matcher-panel-upload" class="matcher-panel">
          <input type="file" id="matcher-file-input" accept="image/*" style="display:none;">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-soft btn-block" id="matcher-upload-btn">Choose a photo…</button>
        </div>

        <div id="matcher-panel-webcam" class="matcher-panel" style="display:none;">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-soft btn-block" id="matcher-webcam-start">Turn on webcam</button>
          <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" id="matcher-webcam-capture" style="display:none; margin-top:10px;">Capture photo</button>
        </div>

        <label class="filter-check matcher-consent">
          <input type="checkbox" id="matcher-remember-consent">
          Remember this photo on this device as my…
        </label>
        <div class="matcher-season-picker" id="matcher-season-picker">
          <button type="button" class="matcher-season-btn is-active" data-season="summer">☀️ Summer shade</button>
          <button type="button" class="matcher-season-btn" data-season="winter">❄️ Winter shade</button>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 12px; margin: 4px 0 14px;">Stored only in your browser's local storage — never uploaded or sent to our servers. View or forget either one anytime from your profile.</p>

        <div class="matcher-frame" id="matcher-frame">
          <video id="matcher-video" playsinline muted style="display:none;"></video>
          <canvas id="matcher-canvas" style="display:none;"></canvas>
          <div class="matcher-placeholder" id="matcher-placeholder">
            <%- icon('user') %>
            <span>Your photo will appear here</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="matcher-status" id="matcher-status" role="status"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Results card -->
      <div class="card" id="matcher-results-card">
        <h3 style="font-size: 20px;">2. Your best match in every product</h3>
        <div id="matcher-results">
          <div class="empty-state" style="padding: 40px 10px;">
            <span class="empty-emoji"><%- icon('lipstick') %></span>
            <h3>No photo yet</h3>
            <p>Capture or upload a photo to see your best-matching shade in every product that has shades.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- face-api.js: free, MIT-licensed, runs entirely client-side on top of TensorFlow.js
       (no API keys, no server calls). Swap this CDN script + MODEL_URL in
       shade-matcher.js for a self-hosted copy under /public/models if you'd
       rather not depend on a third-party CDN in production. -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/face-api.js@0.22.2/dist/face-api.min.js"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/color-science.js?v=<%= assetVersion('javascripts/color-science.js') %>"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/skin-sampler.js?v=<%= assetVersion('javascripts/skin-sampler.js') %>"></script>
  <script>
    /* Server-rendered shade catalog -> plain global the page script reads.
       Swap catalog.getProducts()-derived data (see routes/index.js) for your
       real product/shade data source whenever it changes. */
    window.SHADE_CATALOG = <%- JSON.stringify(shadeCatalog) %>;
  </script>

  <%- include('partials/footer', { pageScript: 'shade-matcher' }) %>
</body>
</html>
